author: julianfoad
msg: Fix typos in tests.  The meaning is not changed.  Although the missing commas
caused the third field to be uninitialised (and therefore NULL) instead of the
intended empty string, that field is not used when the first field is 'd'.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_fs/fs-test.c (check_all_revisions):
* subversion/tests/libsvn_repos/repos-test.c (dir_deltas):
Insert missing commas between array initialisers.

author: breser
msg: Fix warning.
* subversion/bindings/swig/core.i
apr_file_open_stdout and apr_file_open_stderr do not return pointers.

author: breser
msg: Really really really fix the svn_filesize_t warning in the SWIG bindings.
* subversion/bindings/swig/svn_types.i
Use APR_INT64_T_FMT instead of SVN_FILESIZE_T_FMT due to SWIG preprocessor
bug.
#ifdef should have been #if

author: breser
msg: Really fix svn_filesize_t size bug and warnings for perl and python bindings.
* subversion/bindings/swig/svn_types.i
svn_filesize_t is always 64-bits long.  This means it is a long long on
ILP32 platforms and long on LP64 platforms.

author: breser
msg: Stop warnings about apr_time_t on LP64 platforms.
* subversion/bindings/swig/apr.i
apr_time_t is always 64-bits long.  This means it
is a long long on 32-bit and a long on 64-bit.
